  "description": "This test case evaluates the ability to identify patients with chronic kidney disease based on eGFR values and albuminuria levels. The phenotype follows NKF KDOQI and KDIGO 2012 guidelines for CKD staging using G-staging (eGFR) and A-staging (albuminuria). CKD is defined as kidney abnormality present for >3 months.",
